<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>With a required reserve ratio of 10%, what is the maximum amount that can be lent from the 4th deposit in the money creation process, if the initial deposit was $10,000?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">$7,290</option>
            <option letter="b">$6,561</option>
            <option letter="c">$9,000</option>
            <option letter="d">$8,100</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Initial deposit: $10,000 → First bank lends $9,000 → Second bank lends $8,100 → Third bank lends $7,290. Each subsequent deposit is 90% of the previous loan (keeping 10% as reserves). The fourth deposit would be $7,290, and the bank could lend 90% of this amount.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
